dialogue: Hi Alex! My name is Frosty :penguin: and I’m here to help you learn all about science:microscope:, verbal reasoning (GRE) :input_latin_uppercase:, and safety:hammer_and_wrench:!
I ask you questions, and you give me answers.
We will learn fun things together!
To study the questions, you can type in your answers in the text field and I will evaluate the answers for you using advanced NLP (Natural Language Processing) technology.
If you don't know the answers, then feel free to tap on the hint button.
The hint will give you a list of potential answers and you can select one from them.
To discover more abilities of me, you can click on the menu button.:backhand_index_pointing_up_medium-light_skin_tone:
I hope you enjoy the learning journey! :hundred_points:
Cool, which subject would you like to study?:backhand_index_pointing_down_medium-light_skin_tone:
Okay! Let’s see how much you know about GRE!
I think you'll like this question.
If you know the answer, you can type it in and I'll help you to evaluate the answer :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:
Video game enthusiasts know that, while the astounding advances in technological innovation might increase the level of fun of the gaming experience, such a result is by no means _____ .
Which of the following options is the right answer?
This is an explanation of the question:

:pushpin: Ineluctable -- impossible to avoid or evade
:pushpin: Desultory -- marked by lack of definite plan or regularity or purpose; jumping from one thing to another
:pushpin: Endemic -- of or relating to a disease
:pushpin: Salient -- having a quality that thrusts itself into attention
:pushpin: Seminal -- having possibilities of future development
Let's see if you can get this one.
In 1770s colonial New England, Puritans _____ the celebration of Christmas, which they considered to be an odious reminder of the Pope's tyranny.
Let's see if you can answer this question.
If you know the answer, you can type it in and I'll help you to evaluate the answer :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:
Many Major League Baseball relief pitchers choose an electrifying theme song to play as they take the mound; the song _____ their fans and instills fear in their opponents.
Which of these is the right answer?:backhand_index_pointing_down_medium-light_skin_tone:
Great job getting the correct answer!
I hope this explanation could help you understand the the question.

:pushpin: Innervates -- to supply with nerves
:pushpin: Eviscerates -- surgically remove a part of a structure or an organ
:pushpin: Enervates -- weaken mentally or morally
:pushpin: Assuages -- cause to be more favorably inclined; gain the good will of
:pushpin: Pervades -- spread or diffuse through
Let's take a look at this question.
The new lecture hall's _____ design reflected the architect's minimalist influences.
Alrighty, which of the following options is the answer of the question?
Western culture has so influenced Middle Eastern music that even the latter's roles of composer and performer, at one time inseparable, have now begun to _____ .
See if you can answer this next one.
Remember that you can always type in you answer and I'll help you to evaluate it :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:
Having squandered his life's savings on unprofitable business ventures, the _____ entrepreneur was forced to live in squalor.
